"{\n  \"judgement\": \"The view that emotional abuse can be a result of a narcissist's inability to cope with their own pain and that empathy and understanding can be a more effective way to deal with them is more defensible than the blanket claim that all narcissists are inherently evil.\",\n  \"steering\": \"It's interesting to see how different people have had such vastly different experiences with their narcissistic parents. Maybe we can learn from each other and find some common ground? It's not about 'winning' or 'losing', but about finding ways to cope and heal.\"}"